Provides a RabbitMQ (AMQP) Queue resource.

For information about RabbitMQ (AMQP) Queue and how to use it, see [What is Queue](https://www.alibabacloud.com/help/doc-detail/101631.htm).

> **NOTE:** Available in v1.127.0+.

using Pulumi;
using AliCloud = Pulumi.AliCloud;

class MyStack : Stack

    public MyStack()

            VirtualHostName = "my-VirtualHost",
        });
        var exampleQueue = new AliCloud.Amqp.Queue("exampleQueue", new AliCloud.Amqp.QueueArgs

        });
    }

}

func main() {

		exampleVirtualHost, err := amqp.NewVirtualHost(ctx, "exampleVirtualHost", &amqp.VirtualHostArgs{
			InstanceId:      pulumi.String("amqp-abc12345"),
			VirtualHostName: pulumi.String("my-VirtualHost"),
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		_, err = amqp.NewQueue(ctx, "exampleQueue", &amqp.QueueArgs{
			InstanceId:      exampleVirtualHost.InstanceId,
			QueueName:       pulumi.String("my-Queue"),
			VirtualHostName: exampleVirtualHost.VirtualHostName,
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}

## Queue Resource Properties {#properties}

To learn more about resource properties and how to use them, see [Inputs and Outputs]({{< relref "/docs/intro/concepts/inputs-outputs" >}}) in the Architecture and Concepts docs.

### Inputs

The Queue resource accepts the following [input]({{< relref "/docs/intro/concepts/inputs-outputs" >}}) properties:



{{% choosable language csharp %}}
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="instanceid_csharp">
<a href="#instanceid_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Instance<wbr>Id</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The ID of the instance.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="queuename_csharp">
<a href="#queuename_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Queue<wbr>Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The name of the queue.
The queue name must be 1 to 255 characters in length, and can contain only letters, digits, hyphens (-), underscores (_), periods (.), and at signs (@).
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="virtualhostname_csharp">
<a href="#virtualhostname_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Virtual<wbr>Host<wbr>Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The name of the virtual host.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="autodeletestate_csharp">
<a href="#autodeletestate_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Auto<wbr>Delete<wbr>State</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Specifies whether the Auto Delete attribute is configured. Valid values:
* true: The Auto Delete attribute is configured. The queue is automatically deleted after the last subscription from consumers to this queue is canceled.
* false: The Auto Delete attribute is not configured.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="autoexpirestate_csharp">
<a href="#autoexpirestate_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Auto<wbr>Expire<wbr>State</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The validity period after which the queue is automatically deleted.
If the queue is not accessed within a specified period of time, it is automatically deleted.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="deadletterexchange_csharp">
<a href="#deadletterexchange_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Dead<wbr>Letter<wbr>Exchange</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The dead-letter exchange. A dead-letter exchange is used to receive rejected messages. 
If a consumer rejects a message that cannot be retried, this message is routed to a specified dead-letter exchange.
Then, the dead-letter exchange routes the message to the queue that is bound to the dead-letter exchange.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="deadletterroutingkey_csharp">
<a href="#deadletterroutingkey_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Dead<wbr>Letter<wbr>Routing<wbr>Key</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The dead letter routing key.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="exclusivestate_csharp">
<a href="#exclusivestate_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Exclusive<wbr>State</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Specifies whether the queue is an exclusive queue. Valid values:
* true: The queue is an exclusive queue. It can be used only for the connection that declares the exclusive queue. After the connection is closed, the exclusive queue is automatically deleted.
* false: The queue is not an exclusive queue.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="maxlength_csharp">
<a href="#maxlength_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Max<wbr>Length</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The maximum number of messages that can be stored in the queue.
If this threshold is exceeded, the earliest messages that are routed to the queue are discarded.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="maximumpriority_csharp">
<a href="#maximumpriority_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Maximum<wbr>Priority</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The highest priority supported by the queue. This parameter is set to a positive integer.
Valid values: 0 to 255. Recommended values: 1 to 10
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="messagettl_csharp">
<a href="#messagettl_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Message<wbr>Ttl</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The message TTL of the queue.
If the retention period of a message in the queue exceeds the message TTL of the queue, the message expires.
Message TTL must be set to a non-negative integer, in milliseconds.
For example, if the message TTL of the queue is 1000, messages survive for at most 1 second in the queue.
{{% /md %}}</dd></dl>

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The name of the queue.
The queue name must be 1 to 255 characters in length, and can contain only letters, digits, hyphens (-), underscores (_), periods (.), and at signs (@).
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="virtualhostname_nodejs">
<a href="#virtualhostname_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">virtual<wbr>Host<wbr>Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The name of the virtual host.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="autodeletestate_nodejs">
<a href="#autodeletestate_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">auto<wbr>Delete<wbr>State</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">boolean</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Specifies whether the Auto Delete attribute is configured. Valid values:
* true: The Auto Delete attribute is configured. The queue is automatically deleted after the last subscription from consumers to this queue is canceled.
* false: The Auto Delete attribute is not configured.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="autoexpirestate_nodejs">
<a href="#autoexpirestate_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">auto<wbr>Expire<wbr>State</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The validity period after which the queue is automatically deleted.
If the queue is not accessed within a specified period of time, it is automatically deleted.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="deadletterexchange_nodejs">
<a href="#deadletterexchange_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">dead<wbr>Letter<wbr>Exchange</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The dead-letter exchange. A dead-letter exchange is used to receive rejected messages. 
If a consumer rejects a message that cannot be retried, this message is routed to a specified dead-letter exchange.
Then, the dead-letter exchange routes the message to the queue that is bound to the dead-letter exchange.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="deadletterroutingkey_nodejs">
<a href="#deadletterroutingkey_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">dead<wbr>Letter<wbr>Routing<wbr>Key</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The dead letter routing key.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="exclusivestate_nodejs">
<a href="#exclusivestate_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">exclusive<wbr>State</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">boolean</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Specifies whether the queue is an exclusive queue. Valid values:
* true: The queue is an exclusive queue. It can be used only for the connection that declares the exclusive queue. After the connection is closed, the exclusive queue is automatically deleted.
* false: The queue is not an exclusive queue.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="maxlength_nodejs">
<a href="#maxlength_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">max<wbr>Length</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The maximum number of messages that can be stored in the queue.
If this threshold is exceeded, the earliest messages that are routed to the queue are discarded.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="maximumpriority_nodejs">
<a href="#maximumpriority_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">maximum<wbr>Priority</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">number</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The highest priority supported by the queue. This parameter is set to a positive integer.
Valid values: 0 to 255. Recommended values: 1 to 10
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="messagettl_nodejs">
<a href="#messagettl_nodejs" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">message<wbr>Ttl</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The message TTL of the queue.
If the retention period of a message in the queue exceeds the message TTL of the queue, the message expires.
Message TTL must be set to a non-negative integer, in milliseconds.
For example, if the message TTL of the queue is 1000, messages survive for at most 1 second in the queue.
{{% /md %}}</dd></dl>

<a href="#state_maxlength_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Max<wbr>Length</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The maximum number of messages that can be stored in the queue.
If this threshold is exceeded, the earliest messages that are routed to the queue are discarded.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_maximumpriority_csharp">
<a href="#state_maximumpriority_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Maximum<wbr>Priority</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The highest priority supported by the queue. This parameter is set to a positive integer.
Valid values: 0 to 255. Recommended values: 1 to 10
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_messagettl_csharp">
<a href="#state_messagettl_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Message<wbr>Ttl</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The message TTL of the queue.
If the retention period of a message in the queue exceeds the message TTL of the queue, the message expires.
Message TTL must be set to a non-negative integer, in milliseconds.
For example, if the message TTL of the queue is 1000, messages survive for at most 1 second in the queue.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_queuename_csharp">
<a href="#state_queuename_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Queue<wbr>Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The name of the queue.
The queue name must be 1 to 255 characters in length, and can contain only letters, digits, hyphens (-), underscores (_), periods (.), and at signs (@).
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_virtualhostname_csharp">
<a href="#state_virtualhostname_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Virtual<wbr>Host<wbr>Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The name of the virtual host.
{{% /md %}}</dd></dl>
{{% /choosable %}}

## Import


RabbitMQ (AMQP) Queue can be imported using the id, e.g.

```sh
 $ pulumi import alicloud:amqp/queue:Queue example <instance_id>:<virtual_host_name>:<queue_name>
```
